comment.author: 47201412@N02
comment._content: The name of the alley was Matthew Place. The lane led to Upper Fort Street. There is a drawing by Sydney Ure Smith titled 'Corner Matthew Place and Princes St. (demolished)' in 'Glimpses of Old Sydney' by Charles H. Bertie (Sydney : Art in Australia, 1928), plate 3. The lamp post and the lane bollard are not present in the drawing.
